    <h2 class="section-title">Two jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of LG washer service across each environment.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG WM4000HWA, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> LE error code; washer would start a cycle then stop within 30 seconds. Customer had been quoted $650 by another shop for "Direct Drive motor replacement" without on-site diagnostic.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Standard LG LE diagnostic order. Tested hall sensor with multimeter (continuity, signal output through manual rotor rotation): hall sensor reading erratic, intermittent open. Hall sensor confirmed as the LE root cause, not the full motor.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Replaced hall sensor with OEM LG part (in stock on the truck for WM4000 generation). Verified normal motor operation through three test cycles including high-speed spin. Total cost a fraction of the misdiagnosed motor swap quote.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $195 total. Same-day, completed in 90 minutes. Saved customer ~$455 versus the misdiagnosed quote.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>LG WM3900HWA, Rancho Cucamonga</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> OE error and standing water in drum after every cycle. Customer reported the issue had started two weeks ago after a missing-sock incident.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Cleared the debris filter at the bottom-front of the washer. Found the missing sock plus significant lint compaction blocking the pump impeller. Tested pump operation post-clear: pump cycled normally, motor amperage within spec. No parts replacement needed.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Filter clean, sock removal, pump function verification, drain hose inspection. Demonstrated quarterly filter access procedure to homeowner so they could maintain it going forward.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $89 diagnostic only. Same-day, completed in 30 minutes. No parts, no labor charge.</p>
